    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh no, a red blinking light on your router is a classic sign of a connection issue, but don't panic yet! First, try unplugging your router from the power source and waiting about 30 seconds before plugging it back in; sometimes the router just needs a little \"reset\" to clear out any glitches. If that doesn't work, check your modem and cables to ensure they are securely connected, as a loose cable can cause the same red light. If the problem persists, it might be a temporary internet outage in your area, so you could check with your internet service provider to see if they have reported any issues. Keep in mind that while this is a common problem, it's not something a typical human can fix alone; you might need to call a professional technician to diagnose the issue. However, if you are feeling brave, you could try troubleshooting the issue yourself, but be careful not to touch any wires that are not labeled as safe to handle. If you are still unsure, you can always ask a friend or family member for help, as they might have more experience with routers and internet issues.",
